{% extends "_layout.twig" %}

{# It's rare you'd ever want to output the homepage title of so the value here doesn't matter much #}
{% set title = "Reference" %}
{# Set the slug to empty to simulate an empty segment in Craft #}
{% set slug = "reference" %}

{% set external %}
 target="_blank" rel="noopener" title="Link opens in new tab"
{% endset %}

{% block content %}

<div class="w-100 bg-white pad-lg" id="intro">
  <section class="site-container">

    <h2 class="hide">{{ title }}</h2>

    <div data-bk-layout="sm:9 md:8 lg:7 lg:pl:5" data-bk-links="primary underline-hover" class="rte">
      <p class="font-md">Basekit is a front-end toolkit designed for <a href="https://fortytwo.studio" class="arrow-exit" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">FortyTwo Studio</a> web projects, it uses:</p>

      <ul>
        <li><a href="http://gulpjs.com/" class="arrow-exit" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Gulp</a> to optimise and build project files</li>
        <li><a href="http://sass-lang.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Sass</a> for CSS development</li>
        <li><a href="https://twig.sensiolabs.org/" class="arrow-exit" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Twig</a> for HTML/template development</li>
      </ul>

      <p>While templates are built with Twig for later integration with Craft CMS, the core framework does not require Craft CMS.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
</div>


  <div class="w-100 bg-white--tint pad-lg">
    <div class="site-container">

      <h3 data-bk-layout="p:trl" class="font-xl font-light  color-primary">Getting started</h3>

      <div data-bk-layout="lg:8" data-bk-links="primary underline-hover" class="rte">

        <p>Assuming you’ve setup a local server (we rather ❤️ <a href="https://laravel.com/docs/5.4/valet" class="arrow-exit" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Laravel Valet</a>) and you’ve downloaded Basekit to your project directory, <code>cd</code> into your project and run <code>$ npm install</code> to get the required packages.</p>

        <p>Run <code>$ gulp</code> and the magic should start. At the moment this includes: Sass comiling to CSS, Twig compiling to HTML, Javascript to minified and combined basekit.js file, and finally browserSync will kick in. To make use of browserSync visit <em>http://localdomain.dev:3000/demo/</em> and you should see the start page. Remember to configure browserSync the Gulp File.</p>

        <p>If everything went to plan you should be up and running and ready to configure your Sass and Twig.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>


  <div class="w-100 bg-white pad-lg" data-bk-links="primary underline exit">
    <div class="site-container">
      <h3 data-bk-layout="p:trl" class="font-xl font-light  color-primary">Directory Structure</h3>

      <ul class="flex">
        <li data-bk-layout="sm:6 md:4" class="flex">
          <div data-bk-layout class="ba b-grey--light br-1 bg-white--tint flex flex--content-start">
            <h4 class="font-md font-bold pad-xs-b">css</h4>
            <p>The core of Basekit, all your Sass is contained here.</p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li data-bk-layout="sm:6 md:4" class="flex">
          <div data-bk-layout class="ba b-grey--light br-1 bg-white--tint flex flex--content-start">
            <h4 class="font-md font-bold pad-xs-b">demo</h4>
            <p>Static templates and reference documentation get compile here.</p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li data-bk-layout="sm:6 md:4" class="flex">
          <div data-bk-layout class="ba b-grey--light br-1 bg-white--tint flex flex--content-start">
            <h4 class="font-md font-bold pad-xs-b">imgs</h4>
            <p>Logos, placeholders, UI images… but not content images unless the site will always be static.</p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li data-bk-layout="sm:6 md:4" class="flex">
          <div data-bk-layout class="ba b-grey--light br-1 bg-white--tint flex flex--content-start">
            <h4 class="font-md font-bold pad-xs-b">js</h4>
            <p>Numbered project javascript files compile to js/min/basekit.js.</p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li data-bk-layout="sm:6 md:4" class="flex">
          <div data-bk-layout class="ba b-grey--light br-1 bg-white--tint flex flex--content-start">
            <h4 class="font-md font-bold pad-xs-b">node_modules</h4>
            <p>Gulp dependencies, make sure this isn't committed to Git or you’ll not be happy.</p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li data-bk-layout="sm:6 md:4" class="flex">
          <div data-bk-layout class="ba b-grey--light br-1 bg-white--tint flex flex--content-start">
            <h4 class="font-md font-bold pad-xs-b">templates</h4>
            <p>Frontend template files, these compile to the demo/ directory.</p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li data-bk-layout="sm:6 md:4" class="flex">
          <div data-bk-layout class="ba b-grey--light br-1 bg-white--tint flex flex--content-start">
            <h4 class="font-md font-bold pad-xs-b">bower_components</h4>
            <p>Contains and keeps the html5shiv snippet up to date.</p>
          </div>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

{% include '_partials/_pagination.twig' %}

{% endblock %}